  "prompt": "Does money laundering fall under criminal legislation?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a criminal offense in most countries. It typically falls under criminal legislation and is considered a serious financial crime. Specific laws and penalties vary by jurisdiction, but money laundering generally involves:\n\n1. Concealing the origins of illegally obtained money\n2. Transforming illegal funds into seemingly legitimate assets\n3. Disguising the source of criminal proceeds\n\nMost countries have anti-money laundering (AML) laws that criminalize such activities, with potential consequences including:\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Significant fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n\nFinancial institutions are required to implement AML compliance programs and report suspicious transactions to help prevent and detect money laundering activities.",
